@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
title How three epochs feed one epoch's block production

rectangle "Epoch N-2" as E2 {
  [Stake snapshot taken\n= active stake for epoch N]
}
rectangle "Epoch N-1" as E1 {
  [VRF outputs accumulate\ninto the epoch nonce for N]
}
rectangle "Epoch N" as EN {
  [Per slot: pools check VRF;\nelected pool builds + KES-signs\n+ publishes block]
}
rectangle "Epoch N boundary" as EB {
  [Distribute rewards,\ntake a new snapshot,\napply parameter changes,\nprocess pool (de)registrations]
}

E2 -right-> EN : active stake
E1 -right-> EN : epoch nonce
EN -right-> EB
note bottom of E2
  The 2-epoch delay stops an attacker
  from acquiring stake and using it at once.
end note
@enduml
